    "We first compute the flow of metabolite X k from reaction i to j according to:",
    "where Flow þ R i ðX k Þ and Flow À R j ðX k Þ are the production and consumption flows of metabolite X k by reaction R i and R j, respectively.",
    "The set C k contains the indices of all reactions that consume metabolite X k.",
    "The edge weight w i,j is thus defined as the total mass flow between two nodes, aggregated over all metabolites X k that are produced by node i and consumed by node j:",
    "Mass flow graphs allow converting FBA solutions into a directed graph, and thus can be used to represent the network structure of metabolism in different growth conditions or genetic perturbations."
  ]
